---
const lastUpdated = '2026-06-20'

const _jsonLd = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'WebPage',
  name: 'Now — Chirag Singhal',
  url: 'https://blog.oriz.in/now/',
  description: 'What Chirag Singhal is currently working on, learning, and building.',
  dateModified: lastUpdated,
}
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Now — Blog"
  description="What I'm working on right now — current focus areas across the oriz family of sites."
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
  hideSidebar={true}
>
  <header class="page-head">
    <p class="eyebrow"><a href="/">Blog</a> / Now</p>
    <h1>Now</h1>
    <p class="updated">Last updated <time datetime={lastUpdated}>{lastUpdated}</time></p>
  </header>

  <article class="prose">
    <p class="lede">
      A snapshot of what I'm focused on right now — a
      <a href="https://nownownow.com/about" rel="noopener noreferrer">/now page</a>
      in the Derek Sivers tradition. Updated roughly monthly.
    </p>

    <h2>Building</h2>
    <p>
      Maintaining the <strong>oriz family</strong> of static sites — the
      blog (this one), <a href="https://oriz.in">oriz.in</a> home, finance
      calculators, book summaries, image tools, and the cross-post engine
      that keeps RSS in sync with dev.to / Bluesky / Buttondown / Reddit.
      The current batch focuses on consolidating the design system,
      hardening the markdown pipeline (Astro 6.4 + unified migration), and
      shipping the public lifestream that auto-tracks code, reading, and
      health stats — no manual journaling.
    </p>

    <h2>Learning</h2>
    <p>
      Going deep on agentic LLM workflows (Claude Agent SDK, MCP server
      design), Rust-powered build tooling (the new Sätteri markdown
      processor, biome, tokei), and practical Cloudflare Workers patterns
      for free-tier static-first architectures. On the side: distributed
      systems theory and a slow walk through the
      <a href="/series/it-career-guide/">IT career guide</a> series I'm
      writing as I learn.
    </p>

    <h2>Day job</h2>
    <p>
      Backend systems and cloud platforms. Off-hours go to writing,
      building these tools, and reading.
    </p>

    <h2>Where to find me</h2>
    <p>
      <a href="/about/">About</a> ·
      <a href="https://github.com/chirag127">GitHub</a> ·
      <a href="/rss.xml">RSS</a> ·
      <a href="/contact/">Contact</a>
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

